Hello,

We’ve been experiencing odd spikes in our RoboRio CPU utilization.

When we turn on the robot, after about a minute of enabling, the robot will experience nearly 100% of CPU utilization and our CommandScheduler will overrun for a massive 4 seconds; this can lead the robot to drive on its own if the last input it received before the overrun was driving input. This only happens once within the first minute or two of enabling and after that, the robot behaves perfectly.

In our logs, we saw that the overrun comes from our swerve periodic function. When we remove our vision code (lines 281-284), we do not receive overruns, leading us to believe that the error is coming somewhere from that. This is confusing as we have not had issues with our vision in the past.

Here is our code and I attached some log files with overruns below. In the graph, you can see the spike in our CPU utilization. The graphs without spikes did not have vision running. Additionally, you may notice that we got overrun errors right after disabling in some cases–this is because we immediately disabled if we noticed the command scheduler started overrunning. I appreciate any help!

Log files

The issue may be a bit more nuanced than you thought. It is recommended to have AT MOST 1 user thread created as the roboRIO context switching is not the best and takes up alot of time especially when it’s happening every second or less. Consider using Notifier’s instead or adding another periodic loop from RobotContainer.

Based on a glance I would say that’s the biggest problem, i haven’t looked for any Vision processing or opencv stuff in your code yet but if you have anything that touches opencv i would be apprehensive of that too.
